<item>
            <title>[SPARK-10573] IndexToString transformSchema adds output field as DoubleType</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10573</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reproducible example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val stage = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; IndexToString().setInputCol(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;input&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).setOutputCol(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;output&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
val inSchema = StructType(Seq(StructField(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;input&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, DoubleType)))
val outSchema = stage.transformSchema(inSchema)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt;(outSchema(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;output&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).dataType == StringType)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root cause seems to be that it uses &lt;tt&gt;NominalAttribute.toStructField&lt;/tt&gt; which assumes &lt;tt&gt;DoubleType&lt;/tt&gt;. It would probably be better to just use &lt;tt&gt;SchemaUtils.appendColumn&lt;/tt&gt; and explicitly set the data type.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
